  }
  user_input {
    user_response: "I want to build a SaaS prototype for a Shopify AI Agent Control Center.\n\nThe product allows Shopify store owners to connect their store and activate a team of AI agents.\n\nUse the new Gemini Managed Agents concept as the mental model.\n\nThe system should include:\n\n1. A SaaS dashboard.\n2. A Shopify store connection placeholder.\n3. An Agent Registry with the following agents:\n   - Store Setup Agent\n   - Content Agent\n   - Analytics Agent\n   - Theme Development Agent\n   - Design Agent\n   - Customer Support Agent\n   - Media & Digital Agent\n\n4. A Super Agent / Orchestrator UI that receives a user request and routes it to the correct agent.\n\n5. A Tool Gateway abstraction.\nDo not connect directly to Shopify yet.\nCreate mock tools:\n   - shopify.getShopInfo\n   - shopify.getProducts\n   - shopify.getOrders\n   - shopify.getSalesSummary\n   - shopify.prepareProductUpdate\n   - shopify.prepareThemePatch\n\n6. Add an approval queue.\nAll write actions must become pending approval items.\n\n7. Add an audit log.\nEvery agent action should be logged.\n\n8. Add an agent detail page showing:\n   - system instruction\n   - allowed tools\n   - required Shopify scopes\n   - risk level\n   - enabled/disabled status\n\n9. Use a clean modern SaaS UI.\n10. Use Node.js server-side code.\n11. Structure the code so that real Shopify OAuth and Gemini Managed Agents API calls can be added later."
    items {
      text: "I want to build a SaaS prototype for a Shopify AI Agent Control Center.\n\nThe product allows Shopify store owners to connect their store and activate a team of AI agents.\n\nUse the new Gemini Managed Agents concept as the mental model.\n\nThe system should include:\n\n1. A SaaS dashboard.\n2. A Shopify store connection placeholder.\n3. An Agent Registry with the following agents:\n   - Store Setup Agent\n   - Content Agent\n   - Analytics Agent\n   - Theme Development Agent\n   - Design Agent\n   - Customer Support Agent\n   - Media & Digital Agent\n\n4. A Super Agent / Orchestrator UI that receives a user request and routes it to the correct agent.\n\n5. A Tool Gateway abstraction.\nDo not connect directly to Shopify yet.\nCreate mock tools:\n   - shopify.getShopInfo\n   - shopify.getProducts\n   - shopify.getOrders\n   - shopify.getSalesSummary\n   - shopify.prepareProductUpdate\n   - shopify.prepareThemePatch\n\n6. Add an approval queue.\nAll write actions must become pending approval items.\n\n7. Add an audit log.\nEvery agent action should be logged.\n\n8. Add an agent detail page showing:\n   - system instruction\n   - allowed tools\n   - required Shopify scopes\n   - risk level\n   - enabled/disabled status\n\n9. Use a clean modern SaaS UI.\n10. Use Node.js server-side code.\n11. Structure the code so that real Shopify OAuth and Gemini Managed Agents API calls can be added later."
    }
  }
}
