  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Celebrating Initial Success**\n\nThe build completed flawlessly, a truly rewarding initial victory! I\'ve confirmed the implementation of the SaaS dashboard, complete with metrics, detailed summaries, and responsive UI card nodes. The Shopify store connection placeholder is also implemented, featuring editable custom URL inputs. I\'m feeling confident in achieving the requirements as intended.\n\n\n**Confirming Agent Implementation**\n\nI\'ve successfully implemented the Agent Registry, populating it with the seven specified agents, each fully configured with instructions, tools, and risk assessments. Furthermore, the Super Agent/Orchestrator UI is now up and running, featuring an interactive messaging console and dynamic classifier with tool tracking. Lastly, I\'ve implemented the Tool Gateway abstraction, which provides stateful REST interfaces returning mock data for critical Shopify operations.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have built the **Shopify AI Agent Control Center** SaaS full-stack prototype. \n\nThe application is structured to represent a modern control center for Shopify store owners, leveraging the **Gemini Managed Agents** mental model to orchestrate specialized tasks while retaining strict merchant supervision.\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual & UI Design Choices\n- **Slate & Graphite Aesthetics**: Framed by a durable, high-contrast dark graphite sidebar paired with off-white workspaces and generous negative space to promote legibility and a professional developer-tool look.\n- **Micro-Animations**: Features smooth visual state transitions across interactive queues and code diff nodes.\n- **Aesthetic Pairings**: Configured the modern **Space Grotesk** display typography for structural titles, paired with **Inter** for readable body content and **JetBrains Mono** for low-level SDK parameters and JSON output displays.\n\n---\n\n### \342\232\231\357\270\217 Core Modules Crafted\n\n#### 1. SaaS Dashboard Overview\n- Renders the primary status metrics: active agent instances, unread security approvals, and database catalog limits.\n- Features a **Simulated OAuth handshaking link** where the merchant can specify their store\'s custom domain (e.g., `glowthread-apparel.myshopify.com`) and toggle permissions scopes before initiating a mock REST authorization sequence.\n\n#### 2. Managed Agent Registry\n- Instantiates all seven requested specialized agent entities: **Store Setup**, **Content**, **Analytics**, **Theme Development**, **Design**, **Customer Support**, and **Media & Digital**.\n- Selecting any agent displays its metadata parameters: required OAuth capability matrices, allowed tools, and risk tags.\n- Includes a **Dynamic Parameter Tuner** allowing the merchant to toggle agent standby statuses, customize system instruction behaviors, and adjust active tool configurations on the fly. \n\n#### 3. Super Agent Orchestration Chat\n- Interactive console simulated like a control room. Users enter free-text instructions or engage quick-start cards.\n- **Smart Gateway Router**: The request is routed to the correct agent using live semantic classification. If the `GEMINI_API_KEY` is present, it executes real server-side **Gemini API (`gemini-3.5-flash`)** schema predictions to classify targets, form tool arguments, and generate optimized copy. If absent, it recovers with an intelligent, deterministic rule classification engine.\n- Renders the full orchestration trace, printing tool invocation arguments alongside write constraints indicating the transaction is locked.\n\n#### 4. Tool Gateway Sandbox\n- Fully documents the six required developer utility tools (`shopify.getShopInfo`, `shopify.getProducts`, `shopify.getOrders`, `shopify.getSalesSummary`, `shopify.prepareProductUpdate`, and `shopify.prepareThemePatch`).\n- Features a **Mock Run Explorer** allowing merchants to click and fetch live stateful tables from the backend database, displaying real expected JSON schemas instantly.\n\n#### 5. Approval Queue Safeguards\n- All write actions (`shopify.prepareProductUpdate` and `shopify.prepareThemePatch`) are paused inside a secure gate.\n- Renders an interactive **Side-by-Side Diff Viewer** comparing the item\'s previous state vs. the proposed update (e.g., product descriptions overhauled by the Content Agent or responsive layouts modified by Theme Dev).\n- Clicking *Approve* applies the update to the stateful mock database, while *Reject* discards the changes safely.\n\n#### 6. Chronicle Audit Logs\n- Automatically tracks and indexes every system-wide event.\n- Provides searching, initiator filtering, and collapsible triggers to inspect the exact underlying JSON telemetry array of any transaction.\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 2
      nanos: 202385615
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
